E.U. approves 450 million Euros in 'lethal assistance' to Ukrainian military

Doha Madani
11d ago / 9:06 PM UTC

The European Union will finance a large package of "lethal assistance" to held aid Ukraine in its effort to repel Russian forces, Josep Borrell, the E.U.'s foreign policy chief, said Sunday.

Borrell detailed the package to reporters after a virtual media event with other member states' foreign ministers. It is the first time the E.U. has helped finance the purchase and delivery of weapons for a country under attack. 

"We have decided to use our capacities to provide arms ‚Äî lethal arms, lethal assistance ‚Äî to the Ukrainian army by a value of 450 million support package and 50 more millions for the non-lethal supplies, fuel protective equipment," Borrell said. "All these will be covered by our European Peace Facility and intergovernmental fund."

The total package would be more than 556 million Euros.

Poland has agreed to serve as a logistical hub, and defense ministers will meet Monday to discuss how to spend the support package, as well as how to safely transport materials to the Ukrainian front lines, Borrell said.

