11d ago / 8:17 PM UTC

Missiles struck a nuclear waste disposal facility in the Ukrainian capital, Kyiv, but there were no immediate signs of damage or radioactive release, the International Atomic Energy Agency, or IAEA, said Sunday.

The IAEA said the State Nuclear Regulatory Inspectorate of Ukraine informed the agency that the strike occurred late Saturday or early Sunday local time.

The reported strike came less than 24 hours after the Ukrainian government reported an attack on a similar disposal facility near the country‚Äôs second-largest city, Kharkiv, the IAEA said. Again, there were no immediate reports of a radioactive release.

NBC News was unable to immediately confirm the reports.

Russian forces on Thursday captured  the decommissioned power plant at  Chernobyl , the site of the  deadly 1986 nuclear disaster .

